l counterfactuals specifically to software defect generation, grounded in observed runtime behavior. By training DLBL models on such behaviorally plausible faulty examples, we expect significant improvements in generalization, robustness, and precision in localizing actual bugs—especially those arising from subtle logic errors rather than obvious syntax mistakes.

