ll significantly improve model sensitivity to real-world bugs, reduce false positives caused by textual noise, and increase interpretability by aligning model attention with actual fault propagation paths. The impact of this work lies in bridging the gap between symbolic program analysis and neural learning paradigms, offering a principled way to scale high-quality labeled data for software engineering AI tasks. Potential applications extend beyond bug localization to include automated repair, test case generation, and vulnerability detection.",
