ic fault injection, and (3) *feedback loops* where model performance informs future augmentation strategies. It differs from simple code obfuscation or synthetic bug generation by ensuring semantic validity and alignment with actual developer error patterns. Furthermore, by periodically re-evaluating model confidence on augmented data, the system can adapt to temporal shifts in coding practices—addressing concept drift akin to Paper 3’s concerns—making the predictor more robust over time. This idea pushes beyond static augmentation by creating a *living*, self-improving fault prediction pipeline.

